programme.desc: Isaac is a janitor whose livelihood is in jeopardy when his boss tries to cut his job in order to save money. When it seems he has finally gotten the best of Isaac, a misunderstanding at a convenience store puts a winning lottery ticket in Isaac's hands.

programme.title: Complexions
programme.desc: A dark skin aspiring actress is thwarted in love and work all because the color of her skin. When caught lightening her pictures online, her supportive father and light skinned best friend struggle to help her on her journey to love herself.

programme.title: Fixation

programme.desc: Jordyn Dixon returns home to the city of Augusta to reunite with loved ones, but she quickly finds out that things are not the same as she left them years ago. This story follows Jordyn and her circle of friends, who are each on different walks of life in

programme.title: Englewood
programme.desc: Boyz In The Hood is transplanted to the modern day Chicago neighborhood of Englewood in William L. Cochran's powerful directing debut. Englewood boldly blends humor, romance, tragedy, and hope in this tale of three friends struggling to get through high s

programme.title: The Shop
programme.desc: The Shop is an urban drama about two young men, Shawn and Robbie. While running an auto repair shop, Shawn inherits his uncles' '66 Mustang and finds millions of dollars-worth of diamonds stashed in the car. The adoring nephew finds out the truth about hi

programme.desc: Sisters Tracy and Lena are sleeping with each others husbands, Von and Alex. The punishment is worse than the crime when all become entangled in more than just lies and deception, but also murder.

programme.desc: The Legend of Black Annie is a film loosely based on an urban legend. It starts in the late 1960s and ends in 2012. When a group of mischievous boys accidentally kill a young girl, her mother, who is versed in the art of voodoo, enacts revenge upon them a

programme.title: Varnel
programme.desc: Varnel' explores the black male experience from the perspective of Varnel Hill who is an aspiring actor working in corporate America trying to get out to pursue his dream as an actor. Varnel is in his early 30s and works as a mail clerk at a marketing fir

programme.title: Maverick Black Cinema
programme.desc: Maverick is the leading indie distributor of Urban and Black Cinema.

programme.desc: “Bottom Out” is an urban story about average people who, through crime and immoral actions, try to make it good but keep crossing the line between what's right and wrong. Just released from a drug treatment center, Kelly quickly returns back to her crimin

programme.desc: Caught in-between two worlds, Pharaoh has to decide what's more important to him... taking the righteous path...or living the street life. Being loyal to the love of his life, or being loyal to the game.

programme.title: Kaylah
programme.desc: Two worlds collide when a mama's boy prepares for marriage, but cannot shake his mother's grasp.

programme.desc: When Lena coerces her husband, Crutch, to betray, Kane, best friends become sworn enemies. Locked in a deadly battle of mind games, nothing is as it seems, so make your next move your best move, because it could be your last.

programme.title: Maverick Black Cinema
programme.desc: Maverick is the leading indie distributor of Urban and Black Cinema.

programme.title: Beast from Haunted Cave (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: A giant spider stalks a band of thieves in this schlocky thriller from Gene Corman Productions. The story follows gangster Alexander Ward and his crew as they enlist the help of a local ski-instructor in the heist of several gold bars. But when they use explosives to create a distraction, they disturb the lair of a massive spider! Monte Hellman, the man behind such cult favorites as Two-Lane Blacktop, made his directorial debut with Beast From Haunted Cave. Trivia note: This movie debuted on a double bill with The Wasp Woman.

programme.title: Island Claws
programme.desc: When a biological experiment goes terribly wrong, scientists unleash a legion of giant killer crabs.

programme.title: Drive-In Massacre
programme.desc: You'll Pay To Get In... And Pray To Get Out! Two detectives are hell-bent on capturing a demented killer who has been stalking a California drive-in! The film's original poster featured the following: "DRIVE-IN MASSACRE has been deemed by an independent film board to be too terrifying for viewing by the average theatre patron. For this reason, it is suggested that those of you with severe emotional disorders or chronic coronary dysfunction NOT see this movie. The risk is entirely yours." You can't say you haven't been warned!

programme.title: Brother, Cry for Me
programme.desc: Three brothers searching for Inca treasure resort to kidnapping, extortion and murder in this independent thriller. Starring Steve Drexel, Larry Parnell, and Leslie Parrish...

programme.title: The Vampire Bat (1933)
programme.desc: An excellent cast featuring Lionel Atwill, Fay Wray, Melvyn Douglas, and the immortal Dwight Frye headline this macabre tale of vampire attacks in a small village. Does a troubled man-child with an affection for bats have something to do with it? Or is it a local scientist who appears to know quite a bit about vampirism? Director Frank R. Strayer spins a thrilling tale from Hugo nominated screenwriter Edward T. Lowe (House of Frankenstein, House of Dracula) and will have you craving more films from the first golden age of horror!

programme.title: Great Generals - Gen. George Patton
programme.desc: Documentary on General George Patton narrated by Ronald Reagan.

programme.title: Prelude to War
programme.desc: The official testament from the US Government during World War II underscoring why we must fight the various enemies of the Allies

programme.title: The Great Dan Patch (1949)
programme.desc: The Great Dan Patch thunders across the screen in the tradition of great horse movies like Seabiscuit and National Velvet, combining the talents of an all­star cast that includes Dennis O’Keefe, Gail Russell and Henry Hull. But you’ll be hearing more than hoof beats, because there’s plenty of romance in this forgotten treasure from director Joseph Newman (This Island Earth, The Big Circus).

programme.title: Sing Cowboy Sing (1937)
programme.desc: Tex Ritter stars in this rip­roarin’ saga of the Old West! This time, Tex and his pal Duke (played by silent screen veteran Al St. John) square off against a ruthless gang trying to take over the territory’s freight hauling business.The cast includes Snub Pollard, Horace Murphy, and one of the great Poverty Row movie villains of the day, Karl Hackett. Songs include "I’m a Natural Born Cowboy," and "Goodbye Old Paint, I’m ­Leavin’ Cheyenne"...

programme.title: Las Vegas Hillbillys
programme.desc: Ferlin Husky plays a singer who works with a barmaid (Mamie Van Doren) to turn an old Las Vegas casino into a showcase for country music.

programme.title: The Alphabet Conspiracy
programme.desc: A little girl grows frustrated with her homework and dreams the Mad Hatter and Jabberwock of Alice in Wonderland fame have come to abolish the alphabet. Stanley Adams, Frank Baxter, and Hans Conried star in this whimsical tale for director Robert Sinclair (That Wonderful Urge) For trivia buffs: This originally aired on NBC as part of a Bell Telephone educational series, and earned an Emmy for cinematography...

programme.title: Bill and Coo
programme.desc: This peculiar ‘movie’ won an Honorary Oscar in 1948 for its careful blending of “artistry and patience…” Alas, it didn’t inspire more movies acted out by birds. In this one, prolific screenwriter Dean Riesner stepped into the director’s seat for the first and only time, guiding a cast of birdies to tell the story of a town called "Chirpendale," where the peaceful residents are being terrorized by an evil black crow known as "The Black Menace." You’ll have to see it to believe it, but you’ll be charmed by this long forgotten gem.

programme.title: Mr. Imperium (1951)
programme.desc: Lana Turner plays an entertainer who falls for a Crown Prince (Ezio Pinza) in this musical romance from MGM. Marjorie Main, Barry Sullivan, Cedric Harwicke, and Debbie Reynolds also star in this feature directed by two time Oscar nominee Don Hartman (Road to Morocco, The Gay Deception), and boasting music by one of America’s great composers, Harold Arlen! Songs include ‘Andiamo’, ‘Let Me Look At You’, and ‘My Man and My Mule’. (Turner’s voice is dubbed by Trudy Erwin, one of Hollywood’s top ‘uncredited’ singers!)

programme.title: Nothing Sacred (1937)
programme.desc: This classic screwball comedy stars Carole Lombard as Hazel Flagg, a small-town girl who's dying of radiation poisoning. Recognizing the kind of story that sells newspapers, reporter Wally Cook (Fredric March) whisks Hazel off to New York City and turns her into a media sensation. Wally's self-serving plan becomes more complicated when he starts falling for Hazel. Pioneering three-strip Technicolor and smartly written by Ben Hecht and James H. Street, "Nothing Sacred" is a sophisticated comedy brilliantly taking on the media's tendency to put profit before dignity and the simple truth.

programme.title: Father Steps Out (1937)
programme.desc: Joe Hardcastle has it all...a blossoming cheese business...a wife who loves him...and the respect of all around him. Yet, when some society swindlers step in, it's his chauffer that steps in to save the day! Starring George Carney, Bruce Seton, and Dinah Sheridan, this is a "gouda" RKO comedy you won't want to miss!

programme.title: Kansas City Confidential (1952)
programme.desc: In "Kansas City Confidential," four robbers hold up an armored truck, getting away with over a million dollars in cash. Joe Rolfe (John Payne), a down-on-his-luck delivery driver who is accused of involvement in the heist, sets out to discover who set him up and to exact revenge. He follows a trail that leads him to a web of hired killers and corrupt police in Mexico. "Kansas City Confidential" was the source of inspiration for Quentin Tarantino's "Reservoir Dogs." An imaginative film noir classic, this is a fast-paced and highly entertaining gem!

programme.title: Get That Man
programme.desc: A private eye coaxes a chauffeur to pose as a lost heir for his investigation.

programme.title: Long Hair of Death
programme.desc: In a 15th-century feudal village, a woman is accused of witchcraft and put to death. Her beautiful older daughter knows the real reason for the execution lies in the lord's sexual desire for her mother. After confronting the lord on the matter, she, too, is killed. A much younger daughter is spared and taken in by her mother's killers. Once she is of age, as a horrible, deadly plague sweeps the land, she marries the lord's worthless son. Then, during a brutal thunderstorm, the older daughter mysteriously reappears and begins to avenge her mother's death.

programme.title: Manhattan Night of Murder
programme.desc: Special agent Jerry Cotton is hot on the trail of the $100 Gang, a vicious New York crime ring responsible for the murder of a popular restauranteur. Time is of the essence as Jerry races to save the life of the murder's only witness, a 10-year-old boy taken hostage, and bring the gangsters down once and for all.

programme.title: Battle of the Worlds
programme.desc: A runaway asteroid dubbed "The Outsider" mysteriously begins orbiting the Earth and threatens it with lethal flying saucers.

programme.title: Dementia 13 (1963)
programme.desc: Written and directed by a 24-year-old Francis Ford Coppola, "Dementia 13" centers on the dysfunctional Haloran family, who have converged at Haloran Castle to enact a morbid ritual in remembrance of Lady Haloran's (Ethne Dunn) deceased daughter, Kathleen (Barbara Dowling). Secrets shroud Kathleen's demise, and soon there is a mysterious interloper prowling the grounds with a big axe to grind. Genuinely engaging and well-photographed, "Dementia 13" is a bone-chilling horror classic sure to thrill horror enthusiasts and Coppola fans alike.

programme.title: She Gods of Shark Reef
programme.desc: Two brothers, including one wanted for murder, are shipwrecked on an island inhabited by beautiful woman who possess a cache of valuable pearls. What the brothers don't know is that the island women worship a shark god, and are known to make human sacrifices! With a cast that includes the smoldering Lisa Montell, this intense adventure was directed by drive-in movie king Roger Corman. For movie buffs: Corman made the most of location shooting, filming Shark Reef in the same Hawaiian setting as Naked Paradise (1957).

programme.title: The Atomic Brain
programme.desc: Here’s a film, originally known as ‘Monstrosity’ that has lived on thanks to Mystery Science Theater. It was even made into a musical in 2010. It’s quite the ghoulish treat involving a wealthy old woman who wants to put her own brain into the skull of a younger, beautiful girl. The eternal search for youth has never been so grisly!

programme.title: The Fat Spy
programme.desc: Off the coast of Florida, a nearly-deserted island is rumored to have the fountain of youth. A boatload of teenage kids are headed there for a scavenger hunt. Wellington, the island's wealthy owner, is none too happy about that, so he dispatches his daughter, Junior, to get rid of them. She's happy to go because her sweetie, Irving, is the island's only resident. Junior sends Irving to spy on the kids to find out what they know. Irving's twin brother, Herman, and Herman's high-school sweetheart, Camille Salamander, are also headed for the island with their own nefarious plans. Is the fountain of youth real, and if so, who will get to it first?

programme.title: Lawless Frontier (1934)
programme.desc: John Wayne stars in this vintage western about a man avenging the murder of his parents. Other cast members include frequent Wayne sidekick George 'Gabby Hayes', plus Yakima Canutt, Sheila Terry, and Jack Rockwell. This Paul Malvern Production from director Robert N. Bradbury also features Earl Dwire, one of the great B-movie villains, as Zanti, the ruthless bandit who sets the action in motion.

programme.title: Boots and Saddles (1937)
programme.desc: When a young Englishman inherits a ranch, none other than Gene Autry takes up the challenge of turning the Brit into a real westerner. He convinces the Brit to use the ranch to raise horses, but things quickly grow complicated. Look for the usual cast of characters from Republic Pictures, including Smiley Burnette (as the irresistible Frog Millhouse!). Songs include ‘Take Me Back To My Boots and Saddle,’ and ‘Ridin’ the Range.’

programme.title: It's a Joke, Son (1947)
programme.desc: When an egotistical but dim-witted southern aristocrat (Kenny Delmar) runs into financial trouble, his wife (Una Merkel) decides to help by running for state senate. But when he threatens to mess things up, she resorts to having him kidnapped - for everyone's own good! Delmar originally created his character, Senator Claghorn, for The Fred Allen Show radio program. The title of this film is a stock line he would feed to Fred Allen. Claghorn also inspired the creation of Looney Tunes cartoon character Foghorn Leghorn!

programme.title: Death Rides the Sky
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Brother Against Brother
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: Dangerous Waters
programme.desc: In this serial, a criminal called "The Spider" puts Dick Tracy's brother under a hypnotic trance and turns him against the famous detective.

programme.title: My Pal Trigger (1946)
programme.desc: Roy Rogers goes to jail after he’s wrongly accused of killing Gabby Hayes’ horse in this action packed yarn from Republic Pictures. All of the old jokes about cowboys kissing their horse may have started with this very movie, as it focuses on Roy’s loving relationship with Trigger, the greatest horse in all of Hollywood. The film also features Roy’s beloved Dale Evans, plus, adding some country swing to the musical numbers is Roy’s favorite backing band, the Sons of the Pioneers! Songs include ‘Ole Faithful’, ‘Long, Long Ago’ and ‘Livin’ Western Style’.

programme.title: Jackie Robinson Story (1950)
programme.desc: Baseball great Jackie Robinson steps into the lead role in this biopic from director Alfred E. Green (The Jolson Story, Copacabana). Robinson, born in Cairo, Georgia, was the first African American player allowed into major league baseball. The film, which features the cinematography of Oscar winner Ernest Laszlo (Ship of Fools, Airport), is a glimpse into the life of an iconic American sports hero, and his struggles to overcome bigotry. “Mr. Robinson,” wrote The Times’ Bosley Crowther, “... displays a calm assurance and composure that might be envied by many a Hollywood star."

programme.title: Home Town Story (1951)
programme.desc: Leading man Jeffrey Lynn (The Roaring Twenties) plays the downtrodden Blake Washburn, a defeated politician who takes over as editor of a small town newspaper in this comedic romance from writer & director Arthur Pierson. When Washburn discovers the undeniable influence his little paper has on the public, he uses it to appeal to potential voters in the next election. Watch for strong performances from a stellar cast, including Oscar Winner Donald Crisp (How Green Was My Valley), Marjorie Reynolds (Holiday Inn) and an appearance by the great Marilyn Monroe in a small but significant role as Iris, Washburn’s shapely office assistant.

programme.title: Hi De Ho (1947)
programme.desc: Bandleader Cab Calloway, the one and only “Hi­ De ­Ho Man," plays himself in a rousing musical venture involving sexy girls, night clubs, and gangsters! Songs include "St. James Infirmary Blues," and "Don’t Falter at the Altar." Also, look for performances by the Peters Sisters and the lovely Ida James. The beautiful Jeni Le Gon is also on the scene, shaking her tootsies and causing a ruckus!

programme.title: The Pilgrimage Play
programme.desc: Nelson Leigh portrays Jesus of Nazareth in this rare production. This historical saga also stars Richard Hale and John Doucette, and features cinematography by Oscar nominee Walter Strenge (Stagecoach to Fury) as well as music by Oscar nominee Alberto Colombo (Portia on Trial). Movie buffs might be interested to know that make up for this feature about Jesus was done by Jack Pierce, known for creating the faces of the Frankenstein monster, the Wolfman, and the Mummy!

programme.title: Border Patrol
programme.desc: In the mines of Silver Bullet, Hopalong Cassidy helps free a group of smuggled Mexicans from Slave labor.

programme.title: Parole, Inc. (1948)
programme.desc: A government agent goes undercover to battle gangsters who have found a way to infiltrate the parole system in this crime drama from director Aflred Zeisler (Fear, The Amazing Adventure). Several dangerous criminals are unexpectedly paroled, so top agent Richard Hendricks (Michael O’Shea, Lady of Burlesque) poses as a wanted convict to get close to the gang who might be involved; however, gang boss Barney Rodescu (Turhan Bey, The Amazing Mr. X) knows what’s going on. Soon the agent’s life is in danger!

programme.title: Dick Tracy vs. Cueball (1946)
programme.desc: HE’S TERRIFIC! Your favorite crime crusader is back! The second installment of the Dick Tracy film series released by RKO Radio Pictures, “Dick Tracy Vs. Cueball” stars Morgan Conway as the famously unstoppable detective based on the eponymous 1930s comic strip character. When ex-convict Cueball steals valuable diamonds and embarks on a gory killing spree, Dick Tracy allows his girlfriend Tess to act as a buyer for the gems, only to see his plan backfire when the homicidal Cueball captures her. Thrilling and full of mystery, this pulp action film features top-notch performances from Conway and Golden Globe nominee Anne Jeffreys (“Dillinger”) as the lovely and alluring Tess Trueheart.

programme.title: Cause for Alarm
programme.desc: Barry Sullivan plays George Jones, a mentally ill man who mistakenly believes his wife and doctor are having an affair and conspiring to kill him. When he confronts his wife Ellen (Loretta Young), the excitement proves too much and George suffers a mortal collapse. Adding to this delicate house of cards is a letter that he'd written to his lawyer where his fears were outlined. Now it's up to Ellen to retrieve the letter before she finds herself in grave trouble. Bruce Cowling and Margalo Gillmore round out the cast of this suspenseful drama from director Tay Garnett (The Postman Always Rings Twice).

programme.title: The Mad Monster
programme.desc: Prolific B ­movie master Sam Newfield (The Terror of Tiny Town, Dead Men Walk) helmed this tale of a scientist who turns his simple­minded handyman into a raving wolf creature. Why would he do such a thing? To turn the beast on his enemies, of course. Horror icons George Zucco and Glenn Strange star, along with Johnny Downs, Anne Nagel, and Mae Busch. It’s yet another low budget gem from Hollywood’s Poverty Row. Enjoy!

programme.title: My Man Godfrey (1936)
programme.desc: During the height of the Great Depression, a scavenger hunt party game brings a pair of spoiled sisters, Irene and Cornelia Bullock (Carole Lombard and Gail Patrick) to a city dump looking for a "forgotten man." They find down-and-out hobo Godfrey Parks (William Powell), who accompanies one of the sisters back to the party to be presented as a scavenger hunt find, and ends up warily accepting her offer to become the family butler. Irene falls for Godfrey, but is unaware of his mysterious past. Nominated for six Academy Awards, "My Man Godfrey" might be the screwiest of all screwball comedies.

programme.title: White Zombie (1932)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: Invisible Ghost (1941)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi headlines this creepy thriller about an influential man who becomes a bloodthirsty maniac after his wife deserts him. It was the first of nine films made by Lugosi for Sam Katzman of Monogram Pictures, but it’s director Joseph H. Lewis (Gun Crazy, The Big Combo) who elevates this low budget potboiler into something memorable. Aided by veteran cinematographers Harvey Gould and Marcel Le Picard, Lewis creates the perfect atmosphere for this tale of a murderer who strikes in the night and leaves no clues...

programme.title: Teenagers from Outer Space
programme.desc: A young alien and a teenage earthling fall in love, and plot to stop the alien's race from using Earth as a food-breeding ground for giant lobsters from their planet.

programme.title: Carpet of Horror
programme.desc: When a private investigator winds up dead due to exposure to a poisonous gas, his colleagues look to uncover who is behind a string of similar murders in the area.

programme.title: House (1959)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Bird (1955)
programme.desc: Joe and Frank investigate a series of burglaries in new housing developments where the suspect's signature is the killing of pet birds.

programme.title: Echo (1959)
programme.desc: To escape the many questioning reporters, Paul Martin moves to a house in the country after he is acquitted of the murder of his wife. He soon begins to fear for his life, however, and is in for a shock when his late wife’s brother shows up at his house.

programme.title: The Big Squeeze (1959)
programme.desc: After investigating the murder of a mobster, who used to go to school with Mike, Mike hears about a secret meeting of top-tier criminals and plans to take photographs of the meeting.

programme.title: Showdown
programme.desc: After the Virginia City bank is robbed by an outlaw gang, the gang’s youngest member gets a job on the Ponderosa. Initially welcomed, Little Joe becomes suspicious of Ponderosa’s newest member.

programme.title: The Family Tree
programme.desc: Mrs. Drysdale wants to oust the Clampetts in preparation for the arrival of Mrs. Smith-Standish, the head of a 'first family' historical society.

programme.title: The Case of the Eiffel Tower (1955)
programme.desc: A coded note is found in the clothing of a recently killed famous criminal. Holmes works on decoding the note and is sent on a trail of clues to Paris.

programme.title: Flash of Darkness

programme.title: The Ray Baker Story

programme.title: Gets Jealous

programme.title: Proud Father
programme.desc: After running into a friend who brags about his children, Jim hopes to instill inspiration for greatness in his own.

programme.title: Song of Arizona
programme.desc: This Roy Rogers adventure finds Gabby Whitaker (“Gabby” Hayes) running a ranch for wayward boys. One of the boys uses stolen money to help Gabby pay off his debts, but things begin to unravel when the boy’s father, a notorious outlaw named King Blaine, is murdered; the rest of the Blaine gang show up at Gabby’s looking for the loot! Director Frank McDonald works with a fine cast, including Dale Evans, Lyle Talbot, and of course, Roy’s beloved horse Trigger.

programme.title: Brand of the Devil
programme.desc: Three Texas Rangers work together to stop a cattle rustling ring whose known to leave behind a card bearing a pitchfork as a signature for their crimes.

programme.title: Clearing the Range (1931)
programme.desc: Hoot Gibson stars in this reworking of the Zorro legend with a western setting. For trivia buffs: Hoot was married to his leading lady, Sally Eilers, at the time this film was released.

programme.title: The Edsel Show
programme.desc: An hour-long CBS broadcast showcasing Ford's new Edsel car models, "The Edsel Show" is filled to the brim with musical performances, hosted by none other than Bing Crosby and Frank Sinatra.

programme.title: Never Wave at a WAC (1953)
programme.desc: Rosalind Russell stars as a divorced socialite who joins the U.S. Army to be near her boyfriend, only to learn that military life isn’t for everybody. From renowned director Norman Z. McLeod (Horse Feathers, Monkey Business), this riotous comedy also features Paul Douglas and Regis Toomey. They just don’t make comedies like this anymore!

programme.title: Eternally Yours (1939)
programme.desc: Loretta Young and David Niven headline the cast of this comic look at the whimsies of love. Young plays Anita, a woman who breaks off her engagement to go on tour as a magician's assistant. Her decision is exciting as first, but she learns that there's more to life than magic. With an excellent cast that includes Zasu Pitts, Eve Arden, C. Aubrey Smith, Billie Burke, and Broderick Crawford, this fun little comedy was directed by Tay Garnett (The Postman Always Rings Twice) and will leave you baffled by the realities of romance!

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes: Dressed To Kill (1946)
programme.desc: In "Dressed to Kill," three seemingly ordinary music boxes arrive at a London auction house from Dartmoor prison, where inmates construct crafts for income. Sold to three different customers, the boxes soon generate a most sinister interest. When one of the buyers, a friend of Dr. John Watson (Nigel Bruce) is murdered and his box taken, Sherlock Holmes (Basil Rathbone) quickly involves himself in the case. The last of fourteen films starring Basil Rathbone as Holmes and Nigel Bruce as Watson, "Dressed to Kill" is a superb ending to the Rathbone/Bruce series of adventures!

programme.title: Dangerous Passage (1944)
programme.desc: A classic 1940s noir set almost entirely aboard an ominous freighter travelling from Central America to Galveston, Texas. This film revolves around the ill-fated Joe Beck (portrayed by none other than the original Batman, Robert Lowery) as he attempts to retrieve his deceased grandfather’s fortune. With a cast filled out by B-movie royalty like Phyllis Brooks (In Old New York) and Jack LaRue (A Farewell to Arms), this little-known Golden Era gem packs a surprising amount of twists and turns into its 60-minute runtime.

programme.title: Man with Two Lives
programme.desc: The soul of an executed criminal finds its way into the body of a man brought back from death in this thriller from Hollywood’s Poverty Row. Director Phil Rosen (Charlie Chan in the Secret Service) weaves a spine-tingling story with help from a great cast, including Edward Norris (Boy’s Town, Decoy) Marlo Dwyer (The Sniper, Crossfire) and Kenne Duncan (Night of the Ghouls, The Sinister Urge).

When their relationship is put into an uncomfortable spotlight during a friend’s outrageous engagement party, Darren realizes he actually might be self–sabotaging himself due to unresolved insecurities about his sexuality.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Unlikely Family

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Girl-Hearted
programme.desc: It's quite plain to 7 year old Nori: She is a girl, because she has a girl's heart. But her body is that of a boy... Five years ago: Each and every day mother and son argue about what appears trivial: the colours of pants and shirts suddenly matter, soon all he agrees to wear are skirts and dresses, he likes to put barrettes in his still short hair. The neighbours start gossiping. Then one day, the boy reveals his favourite dream to his mum. A wizard will turn his penis into a vagina so he could be a “real” girl ... It's that day something comes to an end. It's that day Josephin realises that she doesn't have a son, that he had never existed – but that there is still a kid, a daughter. It becomes clear to her that she will have to break new ground to see her daughter grow up happily.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.desc: A pre-Madonna primer that raises questions about race, sex and subcultural style, Voguing: The Message traces the roots of this gay Black and Latino dance form, which appropriates and plays with poses and images from mainstream fashion.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Fly Brother
programme.desc: S1 E7 | Ernest eats and explores during the Timkat Festival with friends in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.

programme.title: Fly Brother
programme.desc: S1 E8 | Ernest experiences natural beauty and welcoming culture with friends in Tajikistan.

programme.title: Fly Brother
programme.desc: S1 E9 | Ernest chows down and hits the town with friends in Cape Town, South Africa.

programme.title: Fly Brother
programme.desc: S1 E10 | Ernest explores two cities with good friends in Bogotá, Colombia, and Casablanca, Morocco.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: S1 E21 | Playboy chooses its first gay model; spotlight on new queer music; DC loses only queer LGBTQ center; and Queer Eye gets the LEGO treatment!

programme.title: Davis Mallory | Heavy
programme.desc: The music video for "Heavy" by Davis Mallory featuring Blake Lieder and Daisha McBride. The music video for "Lifeline" by Davis Mallory featuring Allouche. The music video for "Little Victory" by Davis Mallory. A Look behind the scenes at Miami Pride 2021 with Davis Mallory

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E4 | Zach is a track runner and college-bound gay teenager living in Pasadena, California. Once he became more aware of feelings he was having towards other boys, he started running track. It was a way for him to keep his body and mind occupied while he worked through how to deal with being "different." His efforts on the field and in the classroom have gotten him noticed by some top-notch Ivy League colleges.

programme.title: Voguing The Message
programme.desc: A pre-Madonna primer that raises questions about race, sex and subcultural style, Voguing: The Message traces the roots of this gay Black and Latino dance form, which appropriates and plays with poses and images from mainstream fashion.

programme.title: The Billionaire
programme.desc: A gender-swapped independent film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's classic play 'The Millionairess', transposed into a contemporary context of Gay Marriage and Asexuality, THE BILLIONAIRE follows a haughty and prudish young billionaire's quest for love, despite all the odds. The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: The Walk-In Closet
programme.desc: S1 E1-4 | Dana delivers a big package. Sterling receives some very, very scary news./Sterling is very, very sad and drunk; Billie does a Drew Barrymore impression. They come up with a plan!/ It's Billie's straight brother Dom's birthday!/It's time for the first real test! Billie and Sterling meet Ms. Hutchcroft, the immigration official.

programme.title: The Walk-In Closet
programme.desc: S1 E5-8 | Billie goes to "work" at the "comedy" club./Sterling and Billie keep up the super, super good work of passing as straight at the local gym. Dana makes another delivery./Ms. Hutchcroft makes a home visit./Billie and Sterling come to a tough realization.

programme.title: Shutter Rush: City of Abandonment
programme.desc: Three photographers set out to explore the abandoned city of Gary, Indiana. Once on the FBI's most dangerous place to live. Now just a city of ruins.

programme.title: Dropping The Soap
programme.desc: 2017 Emmy Winner, Jane Lynch, Best Actress in Web Series/Comedy. Shit's about to get real for the cast and crew of the long running (awful) soap opera "Collided Lives" when new Executive Producer Olivia Vanderstein arrives to shake things up.

programme.title: Why Can't I Be Me? Around You
programme.desc: Rusty Tidenberg, drag-racing aficionado, shocked friends and family by coming out as trans. Followed for 8 years by filmmaker Harrod Blank (son of Les Blank), Rusty guides us through the aftermath of her transition. Interwoven with lively tales of gender non-conforming individuals on the art-car circuit, Blank’s film is a sensitive and unpredictable love letter to people who fight to be unapologetically themselves.

programme.title: Gina Yashere: Laughing To America
programme.desc: Filmed live in San Francisco, CA, UK's premier black female comedian, Gina Yashere, has come to America! Her unique take on being a cultural insider and outsider never fails to raise the roof as she gives us her take on the news gripping the nation.

programme.title: Baby Steps
programme.desc: From Oscar-winning Producer Li-Kong Hsu (Ang Lee’s The Wedding Banquet, Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon, Eat Drink Man Woman) and Stephen Israel (Swimming With Sharks and G.B.F.), comes this multi-cultural comedy-drama, which takes a funny but honest look at gay family issues in complicated dynamo of a cross-generational Taiwanese and American family. Danny, a Taiwanese-American man, longs to have a baby with his American partner Tate, but their attempts at international surrogacy are complicated by Danny’s meddling mother, who wants to control every aspect of the process -- all the way from Taipei.

programme.title: Strut
programme.desc: In each episode of Strut, we watch Eddie and her friends transform through their risky new endeavor in unexpected positive ways. Eddie is a geeky porn editor whose low self-confidence has turned her into a 26-year-old hermit. Her friends, Eva (an unemployed artist), Lucy (an intern), and Chandaleer (a trainwreck/fashion model) vow to save her from her unhealthy solitude. When the friends decide to start a high-end escorting agency to earn more money, they convince skeptical Eddie to help them build their business and lift her self-esteem. Together they successfully navigate the adrenaline-fueled escorting industry with Eddie as their CEO and fellow sex worker.

programme.title: For My Wife
programme.desc: A feature documentary chronicling the making of an activist. After the tragic death of her wife, Charlene Strong was thrust into the spotlight becoming a powerful voice ;for the equal rights of same-sex couples and their families.

programme.title: Showtime: A Coming Of Age Football Story
programme.desc: A powerful story of the 2019 Parkway North Junior Vikings 8th Grade Team as they strive to become 3 time champions. Despite their differences while learning life lessons through the game of football join together as one team, one vision, one community.

programme.title: Little Miss Westie
programme.desc: If Ren could go back in time before she was four, she would tell her parents that she wasn’t happy living as a boy. Now, Ren is about to take part in a rite of passage for their community in West Haven, CT as the first out transgirl to compete in the Little Miss Westie Pageant. Coaching her through the competition: Her older brother Luca, who previously took part in the pageant when he lived as a girl. Gender dynamics evolve in front of the viewer’s eyes while two transgender siblings explore who they are in this intimate portrait.

programme.title: Drag Kids
programme.desc: Drag has always been about breaking down barriers and daring to do the unexpected. Now, a new type of queen is on the scene: she’s fierce, she’s living in a time of unprecedented access to queer culture, and she’s younger than ever before. She’s a drag kid and she’s a long way from the era of the queens who led the Stonewall Riots nearly 50 years ago. Stephan, Jason, Bracken and Nemis have never met, but they’re united by a shared passion for drag. They are about to come together for the first time – to perform Lady Gaga’s ‘Born This Way’ at the world-famous Montreal Pride Festival. As they prepare for the big show, each faces their own unique challenges, as well as challenges they have in common - deep feelings of isolation and the struggle of trying to claim a place of your own on the fringes of a fringe culture. Drag Kids is a beautiful, daring, and touching portrait of four kids chasing freedom and friendship through the art of drag.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E3 | Victor, Lianna, and Enrique talk about conversion therapy, inclusion in Hollywood with casting director Yolanda Guillen, and living healthy through meal prepping with personal trainer Luis Suarez.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E4 | Writer, Producer, and Director Stan Zimmerman (Golden Girls, Gilmore Girls) and actress Raquenel join us to discuss their LatinX retelling of The Diary of Anne Frank. Plus an interview with the first trans person to run for California state office, Ashlee Marie Preston. Also we discuss LGBTQ voter turnout and how it can improve.

programme.desc: Watch Jennifer Lopez, Angelica Ross, Karamo, Isiah Thomas and Joe Biden on QueerX Live!–the award show, music, and film streaming special for the 2020 QueerX LGBTQ+ film, music, and culture festival. Featuring performances by VINCINT, ROB.B "Heartthrob Robb", Faultlines, Debby Holiday, Shea Diamond, and the winners of the HBO Max Original vogue competition, The House of Balmain, QueerX Live! will screen all the winners of the QueerX 2020 film competition. programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Ep. 16 - Natalie Papillion: Cannabis & The Rise of the Carceral State
programme.desc: Natalie Papillion is a strategist, organizer and policy wonk with nearly a decade of experience building momentum behind brands, causes and candidates. Natalie has worked in both the social and business sectors, including various strategy, marketing and operations leadership roles at Google, Rent the Runway and The Future of Storytelling. Natalie has also worked as a writer, researcher and curator for both academic and mass-market publications, including her forthcoming history “Reefer Madness: The Roots of Drug Prohibition in America”. Natalie is a graduate of Yale University, where she concentrated in the social, cultural and political history of Black communities in the US. Most recently, Natalie has joined the Last Prisoner Project as our Policy Adviser/Director and as a board member. Her most recent work paper, "Criminal Injustice: Cannabis & The Rise of the Carceral State", dives into the sordid history behind America's marijuana laws, and details the staggering human and economic cost of this unjust and ineffective crusade.

programme.title: The Plant Teacher
programme.desc: For centuries, indigenous shamans of the Amazon have sung to Ayahuasca, a psychoactive plant mixture believed to heal the mind, body and spirit of those who drink it. Known as a Planta Maestra, or Master Plant, people from all over the world are now feeling called to experience Ayahuasca and its ancient teachings. As this sacred vine permeates an increasing number of cultures and countries, researchers are discovering that Ayahuasca could help solve some of the greatest problems facing humanity. Exploring the science and the mysticism of Ayahuasca from Western academic and experiential perspectives, The Plant Teacher challenges the limitations and consequences of Western cultural paradigms. It alternatively considers indigenous teachings that seem to extend beyond our current scientific and spiritual understandings, and asks what we could learn if we open our minds to traditional knowledge and medicinal practices. The more we expand our consciousness, the more we realize how little we really know about nature, the universe and ourselves. The Plant Teacher challenges us to open our minds, learn how to truly see, and endeavor to understand the universal interconnectedness that binds us all.

programme.title: Psychedelics: Clinical, Ceremonial & Celebratory: Adapting the Medicine
programme.desc: Throughout human history, psychedelic substances have been used to induce spiritual experiences. Sacred ceremonial use of psychedelics are changing and broadening from intimate Indigenous private Peyote sweat sessions to urban Ayahuasca ritual parties or music festival LSD, Ecstasy and Mushroom intake. How do we educate and safely navigate the growing desire and need for psychotherapeutic environments? And as the medicines are gaining acceptance and legitimacy through research and clinical trials, what does the integration of psychedelics into traditional medicine mean for how we view other indigenous cultural practices and remedies? How can we protect the sacred roots of psychedelic substances while continuing to explore the science?

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor & Comedian Aries Spear
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor comedian Aries Spears. From TV to film, actor Aries Spears spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about recent issues with Mike Epps and a social media post about black on black crime versus police racism against blacks.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Alonzo Bodden
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is standup comedian and former “Last Comic Standing” champion Alonzo Bodden. DL and Alonzo discuss the issues of the pandemic and working as entertainers. They also discuss politics, racism, and other issues in the black community.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Ben Crump
programme.desc: DL Hughley Uncut on GFNTV. Guest on DL Uncut is Civil Rights Attorney Benjamin Crump. Attorney Crump is best known for taking on the toughest cases with national civil rights implications. From Trayvon Martin to Michael Brown, Crump continues to push the envelope for justice for those whose lives have been changed due an unfair legal system.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Charlamagne Tha God
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is one of the hosts on the nationally syndicated radio show The Breakfast Club – Charlamagne Tha God.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest David A. Arnold
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is stand-up comedian, writer and producer David Arnold. He has a special on Netflix called “Fat Ballerina”.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest DJ Doug E. Fresh
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Hughley Uncut is legendary DJ and Hip Hop pioneer Doug E. Fresh. Chris Spencer, the creator of the Real Husbands of Hollywood spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his recent projects and working during a pandemic.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Erika Alexander
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is the brilliant actress from “The Cosby Show” and the 90’s hit series “Living Single” – Erika Alexander. Erika is a producer on the upcoming documentary “John Lewis: Good Trouble” which will release on July 3. DL, Jasmine, and Erika have a great discussion about the creating of “Living Single” and how the show “Friends” became a bigger hit after using the same concept. Erika gives great insight into racism in the entertainment industry.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Leonard Pitts
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is Pulitzer Prize Winner and columnist for the Miami Herald Leonard Pitts, Jr. Leonard Pitts has a progressive voice in journalism who dives deep into the racial and cultural issues of society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Matt Barnes
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former NBA star and 2017 NBA Champion Matt Barnes. Matt discusses his upbringing, thoughts on now legalized marijuana. Matt also gives his thoughts on George Floyd and the affects on our society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tamika Mallory
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Willy T Ribbs
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former race car driver Willy T. Ribbs. Willy was the first African American to test a Formula One racing car and first African American to compete in the Indy 500. DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Lee Merritt
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is attorney Lee Merritt, who is the family attorney for Ahmaud Arbery. Merritt shared the video Tuesday afternoon and said Arbery’s family was forced to watch for the first time online.

programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Space Channel Exclusive- I4's Dr. Sian Proctor
programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Salt Lake City
programme.desc: Westward ho! We settle in Salt Lake City, where we learn about Brigham Young's settlement of the Utah territory and his monument at This is the Place Park. Then we dig in the dirt to find hundreds of perfectly preserved dinosaurs at the Utah Natural History museum.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: Disney Cruise Line
programme.desc: When Disney launched its first ship in 1998, The Disney Magic, it was unlike any other. Painted black to mimic classic ships from the age of cruising, the ship was decked out like only Disney could muster. Disney then bought an island in the Bahamas to serve as a destination for cruise guests only.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Most Unusual Festivals
programme.desc: When it is festival time, it is FUN time. Join Will Clinger and travel coast to coast to discover America’s most unique, enlightening, and unusual festivals. Get in the spirit, celebrate life, and pay homage to our shared cultural history.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: Walt Disney Resort Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Since 1971, Walt Disney World has grown from a theme park and three hotels in Orlando, Florida to a vacation resort of unprecedented size and scope. Today the property encompasses four major theme parks, three water parks, 29 resort hotels, 99 holes of golf, two miniature golf courses, and more.

programme.title: Disneyland Resort: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: It was Walt Disney’s original vision that Disneyland would “never be completed” – always growing and changing. Decades later, Disneyland remains one of the most visited destinations on Earth. Disney Parks has proven its ability remain relevant and continue to be at the very top of the theme parks.

programme.title: Ultimate Walt Disney World
programme.desc: Disney Parks are known for their unparalleled attractions, resorts, and vacation experiences, but when you think of Disney, do you think faced-paced, action-packed, adrenaline-pumping experiences? From the Tower of Terror to Mission Space, and Expedition Everest to Toy Story Mania, get “ultimate.”

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: La Paz
programme.desc: Amid the dizzying heights of the Andes Mountains sits Laz Paz, Bolivia. The Mirandas, the friendly family Alexandra will be staying with, introduces her to elements of Bolivian culture that they keep close to their hearts. Also, meet famous Bolivian chola Glenda Yanez.

programme.title: Ganvie
programme.desc: Welcome to Ganvie, land of the unsubdued, the free, the resistance, and of peaceful waters. In Ganvie, the Tofinu people live on the water. To do so they must move at a careful pace, learn to live without excess, and form deep bonds of family and friendship to survive.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: S7E6 - Paris: Regal and Intimate
programme.desc: In Paris, we'll cruise the Seine River, pay a visit to Napoleon’s tomb, and take in the majestic Louvre. Then we'll shop in a village-like neighborhood, attend church in a pipe organ loft, and celebrate Bastille Day.

programme.title: S7E7 - Paris: Embracing Life and Art
programme.desc: We'll ride a unicorn into the Middle Ages at Paris’ Cluny Museum, get a heavenly look at stained glass in Sainte-Chapelle, go on a tombstone pilgrimage at Pere Lachaise Cemetery, and savor the Parisian cafe scene.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: S7E10 - Venice: City of Dreams
programme.desc: In Venice, we'll sample the splendor of the Doge's Palace, St. Mark's Basilica, Grand Canal, and masterpieces from the Venetian Renaissance — then take a glide on a gondola.

programme.title: S7E11 - Venice and Its Lagoon
programme.desc: We’ll start with a cruise through Venice’s lagoon, pausing to savor fresh fish canal-side. Then we’ll sample the treasures of the Accademia Gallery, explore some back-street wonders, and luxuriate in a venerable cafe on St. Mark’s Square.

programme.title: S7E12 - European Travel Skills Part 1
programme.desc: In this first of three shows focusing on European travel skills, we’ll visit the Netherlands and Germany to learn about transportation by train and car, changing money, and settling in upon arrival.

programme.title: S8E1 - Western Turkey
programme.desc: After kicking off in Kusadası, we wander ancient Ephesus, soak in a natural spa at Pamukkale, learn why dervishes whirl at Konya, and sail the Mediterranean on a "gulet" from Antalya.

programme.title: S8E2 - Central Turkey
programme.desc: In Turkey, we'll marvel at the fascinating landscape of Cappadocia from high above in a balloon...and from deep below, prowling an underground city where Christians once hid out.

programme.title: S8E3 - France’s Loire: Chateau Country
programme.desc: In France's Loire Valley, we'll visit four unique castles — elegant Chenonceau, massive Chambord, stately Cheverny, and fragrant Villandry — with fun stops along the way.

programme.title: S8E4 - Paris Side Trips
programme.desc: After roaming Versailles — the palace of palaces — we'll drop in on exquisite Vaux-le-Vicomte and extravagant Fontainebleau, marvel at Chartres Cathedral...and dine like kings.

programme.title: S8E5 - The Best of Israel
programme.desc: We'll discover the best of Israel, stopping in passionate, traditional Jerusalem, cosmopolitan Tel Aviv, the fortress of Masada, the Sea of Galilee, and the Yad Vashem memorial.

programme.title: S8E6 - Palestine
programme.desc: Exploring Palestine — the Muslim and Arab half of the Holy Land — we'll visit Jerusalem, harvest olives near Ramallah, follow pilgrims to Bethlehem, and bob in the Dead Sea.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: A Taste of Tokyo
programme.desc: Anthony travels to Tokyo, where he begins in the Tsujiki market and then is introduced to techniques in preparing edomae sushi. He also learns the diets of Sumo wrestlers.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Puebla, Where the Good Cooks Are From
programme.desc: Puebla, Mexico: According to Tony, the best line cooks in NYC come from Mexico, so he travels to the Puebla, and enjoys mole sauces, toasted ant eggs, fried worms, and the legendary pulque (a slightly hallucinogenic drink made from cactus sap).

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: S8E3 - Cooking on the Sea of Cortez
programme.desc: Rick is always up for a cooking challenge, and after a day on the waters of the Sea of Cortez, Rick grills dinner for the group on the beach of Espiritu Santo Island. To stock up on supplies Rick shops in the La Paz market for ingredients.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: Ganvie
programme.desc: Welcome to Ganvie, land of the unsubdued, the free, the resistance, and of peaceful waters. In Ganvie, the Tofinu people live on the water. To do so they must move at a careful pace, learn to live without excess, and form deep bonds of family and friendship to survive.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Aarhus
programme.desc: Welcome to Aarhus, Denmark, a city that illuminates the essential societal values Dans hold dear, values that include trust and honesty, health and happiness, and a strong belief in your fellow people. Alexandra comes to find out that collaboration can lead to prosperity.

programme.title: S8E1 - Western Turkey
programme.desc: After kicking off in Kusadası, we wander ancient Ephesus, soak in a natural spa at Pamukkale, learn why dervishes whirl at Konya, and sail the Mediterranean on a "gulet" from Antalya.

programme.title: S8E2 - Central Turkey
programme.desc: In Turkey, we'll marvel at the fascinating landscape of Cappadocia from high above in a balloon...and from deep below, prowling an underground city where Christians once hid out.

programme.title: S8E3 - France’s Loire: Chateau Country
programme.desc: In France's Loire Valley, we'll visit four unique castles — elegant Chenonceau, massive Chambord, stately Cheverny, and fragrant Villandry — with fun stops along the way.

programme.title: S8E4 - Paris Side Trips
programme.desc: After roaming Versailles — the palace of palaces — we'll drop in on exquisite Vaux-le-Vicomte and extravagant Fontainebleau, marvel at Chartres Cathedral...and dine like kings.

programme.title: S8E5 - The Best of Israel
programme.desc: We'll discover the best of Israel, stopping in passionate, traditional Jerusalem, cosmopolitan Tel Aviv, the fortress of Masada, the Sea of Galilee, and the Yad Vashem memorial.

programme.title: S8E6 - Palestine
programme.desc: Exploring Palestine — the Muslim and Arab half of the Holy Land — we'll visit Jerusalem, harvest olives near Ramallah, follow pilgrims to Bethlehem, and bob in the Dead Sea.

programme.title: S8E7 - Italy's Riviera: Cinque Terre
programme.desc: We'll visit Italy's five tiny seaside towns known as the Cinque Terre, while stopping to fish for anchovies, sip wine from barrels, and savor twinkling Mediterranean vistas.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: S7E6 - Paris: Regal and Intimate
programme.desc: In Paris, we'll cruise the Seine River, pay a visit to Napoleon’s tomb, and take in the majestic Louvre. Then we'll shop in a village-like neighborhood, attend church in a pipe organ loft, and celebrate Bastille Day.

programme.title: S7E7 - Paris: Embracing Life and Art
programme.desc: We'll ride a unicorn into the Middle Ages at Paris’ Cluny Museum, get a heavenly look at stained glass in Sainte-Chapelle, go on a tombstone pilgrimage at Pere Lachaise Cemetery, and savor the Parisian cafe scene.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: S7E10 - Venice: City of Dreams
programme.desc: In Venice, we'll sample the splendor of the Doge's Palace, St. Mark's Basilica, Grand Canal, and masterpieces from the Venetian Renaissance — then take a glide on a gondola.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig

programme.desc: Anthony travels to Tokyo, where he begins in the Tsujiki market and then is introduced to techniques in preparing edomae sushi. He also learns the diets of Sumo wrestlers.
